---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — SolarROI"
  description="How SolarROI handles your data. Plain English."
>
  <header class="border-b border-solar-hairline">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 font-bold tracking-tight">
        <span
          class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-solar-orange"
          aria-hidden="true"></span>
        SolarROI
      </a>
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-solar-muted">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Home</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <p
      class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-3"
    >
      Privacy Policy
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">
      We keep it simple.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-solar-muted">
      Last updated: April 26, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="prose mt-12 text-solar-ink leading-relaxed space-y-6 text-[17px]">
      <p>
        SolarROI is an iOS app that helps solar contractors generate proposals
        for their customers. This page explains, in plain English, what data
        the app handles and where it goes. If anything below is unclear,
        email <a class="text-solar-orange underline" href="mailto:support@solarroi.app">support@solarroi.app</a>
        and we'll fix it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">What we don't do</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>No accounts. SolarROI does not require you to sign up or sign in.</li>
        <li>No analytics SDKs, no third-party trackers, no advertising networks.</li>
        <li>No data is sent to SolarROI's own servers — we don't run any.</li>
        <li>No customer data is uploaded for marketing or any other purpose.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Data stored on your device</h2>
      <p>
        Everything you enter into SolarROI is stored locally on your iPhone or
        iPad. It is not synced to a SolarROI cloud, because there is no
        SolarROI cloud. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Your contractor profile</strong> — company name, contact
          name, license number, phone, email, website, and business address.
          Stored in iOS user defaults.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Your custom watermark image</strong> (Pro feature), if
          you've uploaded one. Stored in iOS user defaults.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Your customer projects</strong> — customer name and contact
          info, customer address, system size, tilt, azimuth, roof type,
          module type, financial inputs, and the production / financial
          results SolarROI calculates. Saved as JSON files in the app's
          private Documents directory.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Your default rates</strong> — cost per watt, utility rate,
          escalator, ITC percent, default losses.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is included in standard iOS / iCloud device backups (because
        Apple backs up app data by default). It never leaves your device
        through SolarROI.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Data sent to third parties</h2>
      <p>
        To produce a proposal, SolarROI talks to two services on your behalf.
        Both are well-known and operate under their own privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-6">1. Apple — geocoding</h3>
      <p>
        When you enter a customer address, SolarROI uses Apple's CLGeocoder
        (the same component Apple Maps uses) to convert that address into
        latitude and longitude. This is an iOS system service. The address
        text is sent to Apple. SolarROI does not control how Apple processes
        these requests — see Apple's privacy policy for details.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-6">2. NREL — solar production estimates</h3>
      <p>
        SolarROI calls the National Renewable Energy Laboratory's PVWatts v8
        API (<code>developer.nrel.gov</code>) to estimate how much electricity
        a given system will produce at a given site. We send NREL:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>The latitude and longitude of the project site</li>
        <li>System capacity in kW, tilt, azimuth, array type, module type, and losses</li>
        <li>An NREL API key</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Customer names, addresses, contact info, and pricing are
        <strong>not</strong> sent to NREL — only the numeric site and system
        parameters needed for the simulation. By default the app uses NREL's
        public <code>DEMO_KEY</code>; if you provide your own NREL API key in
        Settings, it is stored locally on your device and used in place of
        <code>DEMO_KEY</code>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold mt-6">3. Apple — subscription processing</h3>
      <p>
        SolarROI Pro ($4.99/month) is sold through Apple's StoreKit. Apple
        handles the entire transaction: payment method, billing, tax, and
        renewals. SolarROI never sees your payment information. We only
        receive a signal from Apple confirming whether your subscription is
        currently active.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">PDFs you generate</h2>
      <p>
        When you export a PDF proposal, that file is generated entirely
        on-device and handed to iOS's standard share sheet. Where it goes
        next — Mail, Messages, AirDrop, Files, a third-party app — is up to
        you. SolarROI does not retain a copy beyond the project record on
        your device.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Children</h2>
      <p>
        SolarROI is a tool for professional solar contractors. It is not
        directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
        information from children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Your control</h2>
      <p>
        Because data lives on your device, you control it. Delete a project
        from inside SolarROI to remove it. Delete the app to remove
        everything (contractor profile, projects, watermark, settings).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we change how the app handles data, we'll update this page and
        bump the date at the top. For material changes, we'll also note them
        in the App Store release notes.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? Email
        <a class="text-solar-orange underline" href="mailto:support@solarroi.app"
          >support@solarroi.app</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
